incident_trace_root: FT-CHECKOUT -> INC-001 -> INC-010 -> INC-020 -> INC-030 -> INC-040 -> INC-050 -> INC-060

@map
- INC-000 | Input Guide | Quick rules for what to fill in this document
- INC-001 | Problem Section Tagging | Pin the affected feature and section first
- INC-010 | Bug Situation Capture | Record repro conditions and observed symptoms
- INC-020 | Fast Root-Cause Analysis | Build first-pass cause conclusion from evidence
- INC-030 | Improvement Direction | Decide fix options, priority, and risk
- INC-040 | AI Work Handoff Request | Write an execution-ready handoff for AI
- INC-050 | AI Work Result Summary | Summarize AI changes and touched points
- INC-060 | Validation and Closure Decision | Confirm close/follow-up decision with evidence

@section INC-000
title: Input Guide
summary: Minimum input rules for consistent writing by humans and AI
links: GUIDE-INPUT
content:
<<<
[Required input]
1) Fill every blank after -, 1), and : with concrete content.
2) Use specific numbers, dates, owners, and evidence whenever possible.
3) If unknown, do not leave blank; write TBD (needs confirmation).

[AI request contract]
- target_docs: actual file path
- target_sections: section IDs or section paths
- goal: why this change is needed (1-2 sentences)
- constraints: scope/forbidden constraints
- done: validation-based completion criteria

[AI output contract]
- Changed files / Changed sections / Reason / Impact / Risks / Validation

[Done checklist]
- Are @map rows and @section IDs aligned?
- For edits, is @change reason/impact recorded?
>>>

@section INC-001
title: Problem Section Tagging
summary: Lock the incident to a feature tag and section ID before deep investigation
links: INCIDENT-TAG-001
